eu.cassandra.sim
Class Simulation

java.lang.Object
  eu.cassandra.sim.Simulation
Direct Known Subclasses:
MySimpleDynamicScenarioSimulation, MySimpleStaticScenarioSimulation, StandAloneSimulation
public abstract class Simulation
extends java.lang.Object

The Simulation class includes methods for setting up the scenario to be simulated and running the simulation, provided the implementation of the abstract setupScenario() method. It can simulate up to 4085 years.

The implementation of the setupScenario() method must include:
(a) setting up the installations (or installation types) to be included in the simulation,
(b) setting up the pricing scheme(s) to be used in the simulation,
(c) defining the set of simulation parameters to be used and, in case of dynamic scenarios,
(d) the demographic data, according to which the entities involved in the simulation will be instantiated.

After providing the implementation of the setupScenario() method, the setup() and runSimulation() methods need to be called, in order to instantiate the entities involved in the scenario and simulate it.

Author:
Kyriakos C. Chatzidimitriou (kyrcha [at] iti [dot] gr), Fani A. Tzima (fani [dot] tzima [at] iti [dot] gr)

Method Detail

setupScenario

public abstract java.util.Vector<Installation> setupScenario()
Abstract method for setting up a scenario. The implementation of the method must include:
(a) setting up the installations (or installation types) to be included in the simulation,
(b) setting up the pricing scheme(s) to be used in the simulation,
(c) defining the set of simulation parameters to be used and, in case of dynamic scenarios,
(d) the demographic data, according to which the entities involved in the simulation will be instantiated.

Returns:
the vector of installation (types) to be used in the simulation

setup

public void setup(boolean isCallDuringRun)
           throws java.lang.Exception
Sets the scenario up according to the setupScenario method and instantiates all involved entities, taking into account the nature (static or dynamic) of the scenario and, when applicable, the demographic data provided.

Parameters:
isCallDuringRun - whether this call to the method happens during the run or not
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - the exception

runSimulation

public void runSimulation()
Runs the simulation and outputs results to the csv files and the selected database. Results include the expected, active and reactive power per installation, along with various KPIs that can be printed out using the printKPIs method.
